      ],
      "explanation": "Banks evaluate business loans using the '5 Cs of credit': Character (credit history), Capacity (cash flow to repay), Capital (owner's investment), Collateral (assets to secure the loan), and Conditions (loan purpose and economic environment). For small businesses, the owner's personal credit and a personal guarantee are often required because the business lacks sufficient standalone credit history."
